title: Print, "Plate in Vasses de la Maison Royalle de L'oo Nouvellement (Vessels of the Royal House of L'oo)", ca. 1700
medium: Etching and engraving on white laid paper
signed: Signed in plate, lower right: inventé et gravé par D. Marot.
inscribed: Inscribed in plate, lower left: avec Preuilege des Etats Generaux.
dimensions:
Sheet: 35 x 23.5 cm (13 3/4 x 9 1/4 in.)
Platemark: 26.1 x 20 cm (10 1/4 x 7 7/8 in.)
creditline: Museum purchase from General Acquisitions Endowment Fund
description: Footed vessel on a pedestal decorated with a cartouche depicting three classical female figures and one putto next to a tree. At each corner of the vessel are draped female caryatids in different poses.
